Mac NID 6

IBM Plex Sans Thin Italic (IBMPlexSans-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Sans Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

IBM Plex Sans Thin Italic (IBMPlexSans-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSans-ThinItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

IBM Plex Sans Thin Italic (IBMPlexSans-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Sans Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Sans ExtraLight Italic (IBMPlexSans-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Sans ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Sans ExtraLight Italic (IBMPlexSans-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSans-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Sans ExtraLight Italic (IBMPlexSans-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Sans ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

NID 16 'IBM Plex Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Sans Light'.

Pass

IBM Plex Sans Light Regular (IBMPlexSans-Light.ttf)

NID 16 does not contain any of the following keywords: 'Book, Ultra, Normal'

IBM Plex Sans Light Italic (IBMPlexSans-LightItalic.ttf)

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSans-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

name

Mac NID 6

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSans-Italic', Everything looks good.

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSans-Medium', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Sans Medium Regular (IBMPlexSans-Medium.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Sans Medium'.

Pass

IBM Plex Sans Medium Italic (IBMPlexSans-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Sans Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

IBM Plex Sans Medium Italic (IBMPlexSans-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSans-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Sans Medium Italic (IBMPlexSans-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Sans Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

IBM Plex Sans SemiBold Regular (IBMPlexSans-SemiBold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Sans SemiBold'.

IBM Plex Sans SemiBold Regular (IBMPlexSans-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Sans SemiBold'.

Pass

IBM Plex Sans SemiBold Italic (IBMPlexSans-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

IBM Plex Sans Bold (IBMPlexSans-Bold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSans-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

IBM Plex Sans Thin Regular (IBMPlexSans-Thin.ttf)

GSUB

sinf

If there is a feature subs, then the sinf feature should be there, too. Otherwise InDesign will mark it not existing.

OK: There is a subs and sinf feature in the font.

Error

IBM Plex Sans Thin Regular (IBMPlexSans-Thin.ttf)

name

Friendly Name

Check Friendly Stylistic Set Name according Monotype Standards.

Please double check with the following list, if
'ss01' = 'simple lowercase a'
is a valid name according MT.
More infos here:
